From cdfb2d3ab48c674cde6e8340d56e3cd98d42206e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: reardonia <2925104+reardonia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Apr 2026 21:12:08 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 04/21] LinuxRendererGL/GLES: rename YV12 helpers to reflect
 actual formats

The Create/Delete/Upload helpers named after YV12 have handled
YUV420P, YUV422P, and now YUV444P planar formats, and the ring
buffer state named m_iYV12RenderBuffer / m_NumYV12Buffers was
always format-agnostic. Rename to match what the code actually
does.

Function families:
 CreateYV12Texture        -> CreatePlanarYUVTexture
 DeleteYV12Texture        -> DeletePlanarYUVTexture
 UploadYV12Texture        -> UploadPlanarYUVTexture
 CreateYUV422PackedTexture -> CreatePackedYUVTexture
 DeleteYUV422PackedTexture -> DeletePackedYUVTexture
 UploadYUV422PackedTexture -> UploadPackedYUVTexture

Ring buffer state:
 m_iYV12RenderBuffer -> m_iYUVRenderBuffer
 m_NumYV12Buffers    -> m_NumYUVBuffers
 NextYV12Texture     -> NextYUVTexture
 SkipUploadYV12      -> SkipUploadYUV

No behavior change. SHADER_YV12 enum values are left untouched
(their rename would cascade into shader files and other renderers).
